BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State African American Cultural Center
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Student Life
DESCRIPTION:The African American Cultural Center\, LGBTQ Pride Center\, Wom
 en's Center\, Multicultural Student Affairs and the NC State Libraries have
  joined together to host a semester-long book club. The club will read and 
 discuss the award-winning book\, Song In a Weary Throat by Pauli Murray\, t
 hroughout the spring semester. A different student success center will host
  each month's book club session. The book club will visit the Pauli Murray 
 Center.\n\nThe first 20 people to sign up for the book club will receive a 
 free book and reading kit curated by the African American Cultural Center L
 ibrary\, Multicultural Students Affairs\, the Women’s Center\, the LGBTQ Pr
 ide Center and the NC State Libraries.\n\nThe book club sessions will take 
 place:\n\nJan. 22 from noon to 2 p.m. in the LGBTQ Pride Center at Talley S
 tudent UnionJoin us for a meet and greet and introduction to Song in a Wear
 y Throat.Feb. 5 from noon to 2 p.m. in the African Cultural Center Library 
 at the Witherspoon Student CenterWe will discuss chapters 1-3 and 7 and 8.F
 eb. 24 from noon to 2 p.m. in Multicultural Student Affairs at Talley Stude
 nt UnionWe will discuss chapters 9\, 11\, 15\, 16 and 19.March 24 from noon
  to 2 p.m. in the Women’s Center at Talley Student UnionWe will discuss cha
 pters 20-22\, 24-25 and 26. April 7 from noon to 2 p.m. in the Fishbowl at 
 D.H. Hill LibraryWe will discuss chapters 27\, 29-30 and 34.
DTEND:20260324T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260408T030600Z
DTSTART:20260324T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Rainbow Reading Group: Song in A Weary Throat by Pauli Murray
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51808672376727
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/rainbow-reading-group-song-in-a-weary-t
 hroat-by-pauli-murray
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State African American Cultural Center
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Community Events,Student Life
DESCRIPTION:Join the African American Cultural Center (AACC) for a session 
 on how the NC State Libraries can support your academic\, professional and 
 personal growth. You will engage with authors and librarians to learn how t
 o leverage library resources and spaces and the expertise of its staff.  Yo
 u will also explore opportunities for research and creative projects and le
 arn why representation in collections is important.\n\nThe event will offer
  insights for anyone interested in research\, writing or lifelong learning.
  However\, it will be particularly valuable for students majoring in Englis
 h\, history\, journalism\, sociology\, anthropology\, political science\, p
 sychology\, arts and information science. You'll leave with practical strat
 egies\, new connections and inspiration to explore yourself and the world a
 round you. Student attendees will have a chance to win one of two Patron Pr
 ize kits containing limited-edition AACC Library swag\, a free book\, libra
 ry starter materials and more.\n\nThis event will close with a book signing
  by Zelda Lockhart and C.M. Lockhart. You can buy their books at the event 
 or bring your own copies. The first 20 students to register for the event w
 ill receive a free book by Zelda Lockhart or C.M. Lockhart.\n\nAll are welc
 ome to attend. The event is part of the AACC's celebration of National Libr
 ary Week.
DTEND:20260407T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260408T030600Z
DTSTART:20260406T220000Z
GEO:35.785108;-78.674529
LOCATION:Witherspoon Student Center\, African American Cultural Center Gall
 ery and Library (218)
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Libraries as Spaces of Opportunity Panel
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52456155275443
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/libraries-as-spaces-of-opportunity-pane
 l
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State African American Cultural Center
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Workshops and Training,Community Events,Stude
 nt Life
DESCRIPTION:Join the African American Cultural Center (AACC) for its Spring
  Learning Labs\, a dynamic workshop series designed to help students build 
 skills and explore their creativity. Each hands-on session is a supportive 
 space for you to connect with peers\, learn from passionate facilitators\, 
 and grow your talents.\n\nFuel your brain and your stomach at the AI and Ap
 petizers session. During this workshop\, you’ll learn how to use artificial
  intelligence responsibly\, which AI tools you have access to as an NC Stat
 e student and how to leverage those tools for personal and professional pro
 jects. Bring your laptop and your curiosity. Refreshments and light appetiz
 ers will be available.\n\nThis event is part of the AACC's celebration of N
 ational Library Week. Student attendees will have a chance to win one of tw
 o Patron prize kits containing limited-edition AACC Library swag\, a free b
 ook\, library starter materials and more.
DTEND:20260407T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260408T030600Z
DTSTART:20260407T213000Z
GEO:35.785108;-78.674529
LOCATION:Witherspoon Student Center\, African American Cultural Center Libr
 ary (218)
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Learning Lab: AI and Appetizers
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52456237124059
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/learning-lab-ai-and-appetizers-3875
END:VEVENT
