BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State African American Cultural Center
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Exhibitions,Student Life
DESCRIPTION:Windows Into the Soul is an exhibition highlighting the powerfu
 l role that libraries\, special collections and historical sites play in ex
 panding access to African American and Afro-diasporic culture\, knowledge a
 nd lived experiences. The exhibition will feature materials from Triangle-a
 rea libraries and special collections\, including NC State and Shaw univers
 ities. It will showcase rare books\, photographs\, archival records\, oral 
 histories\, creative works and community ephemera that illuminate the richn
 ess of African American life and expression.\n\nThe exhibition is part of t
 he African American Cultural Center's celebration of National Library Week.
  Visitors of all backgrounds are welcome to come explore how libraries and 
 archives preserve stories\, expand access to knowledge and support deeper u
 nderstanding across communities. The exhibit will be available to view Apri
 l 8–10 from 11 a.m. to 5 p.m.\n\nA closing reception that will feature rema
 rks by exhibit partners will be held April 10 from noon to 2 p.m. Refreshme
 nts will be served at the reception. Student attendees will have a chance t
 o win one of two Patron prize kits containing limited-edition AACC Library 
 swag\, a free book\, library starter materials and more.\n\nAll are welcome
  to come see the exhibit and attend the reception.
DTEND:20260408T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260408T030600Z
DTSTART:20260408T150000Z
GEO:35.787562;-78.669711
LOCATION:D.H. Hill Jr. Library\, Cyma Rubin Visualization Gallery
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:African American Libraries and Collections Exhibit
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52461070102606
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/windows-into-the-soul-african-american-
 libraries-and-collections-exhibit
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State African American Cultural Center
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Training,Community Events,Student Life
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in conducting research and want to become a 
 research scholar\, but you are unsure how to start? Are you curious about w
 hat it’s like to present at the African American Cultural Center's (AACC) a
 nnual Symposium on Afrofuturism and Diasporic Scholarship?\n\nIf you answer
 ed yes to those questions\, the AACC invites you to attend an informal sess
 ion on all things research. You'll enjoy a catered lunch with undergraduate
 \, graduate and faculty scholars who have presented at past AACC symposiums
 . You'll also have the opportunity to talk to research experts from the NC 
 State University Libraries and the Office of Undergraduate Research.\n\nThi
 s session is part of the AACC's celebration of National Library Week. Stude
 nt attendees will have a chance to win one of two Patron prize kits contain
 ing limited-edition AACC Library swag\, a free book\, library starter mater
 ials and more.
DTEND:20260408T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260408T030600Z
DTSTART:20260408T160000Z
GEO:35.785108;-78.674529
LOCATION:Witherspoon Student Center\, African American Cultural Center Libr
 ary (218)
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Becoming a Researcher: Stories and Advice From Scholars
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52456379991330
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/becoming-a-researcher-stories-and-advic
 e-from-scholars
END:VEVENT
