BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State African American Cultural Center
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Join African American Cultural Center Librarian Wynter Douglas 
 on April 9\, from noon to 1:30 p.m. at the LGBTQ Pride Center for the final
  Rainbow Reading Chat of the semester. The session will feature a discussio
 n about the amazing Black lesbian\, mother\, warrior\, poet and librarian A
 udre Lorde. You’ll learn about her life and create an outline for your pers
 onal biomythography\, a writing genre that Lorde invented that blends mytho
 logy\, history and fantasy.\n\nThis Rainbow Reading Chat is part of the Afr
 ican American Cultural Center's celebration of National Library Week. Four 
 attendees will win a book. All are welcome to come\, chat and reclaim your 
 personal story.
DTEND:20260409T173000Z
DTSTAMP:20260408T030600Z
DTSTART:20260409T160000Z
GEO:35.784114;-78.671321
LOCATION:Talley Student Union\, Suite 5230
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Rainbow Reading Chat: Audre Lorde and Biomythography
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51929860900765
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/rainbow-reading-chat-queer-afrofuturism
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC State African American Cultural Center
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Training,Community Events,Student Life
DESCRIPTION:Join the African American Cultural Center (AACC) for a hands-on
  workshop to learn how to bookbind\, have community conversations and start
  building a library of your thoughts\, stories and reading reflections. Lib
 rarian Beatrice Downey will begin the workshop with a short presentation on
  sustaining reading as a lifelong habit and recording your reading journeys
  through journaling and Instagram. Participants will create a collage with 
 fun materials\, images of Black student life at NC State provided by the Sp
 ecial Collections Research Center and quotes from Black authors curated by 
 the African American Cultural Center's librarian.\n\nAttendees will meet ar
 chivists and preservationists from the Special Collections Research Center 
 and get a glimpse into their careers.\n\nStudent attendees will have a chan
 ce to win one of two Patron prize kits containing limited-edition AACC Libr
 ary swag\, a free book\, library starter materials and more.\n\nThe worksho
 p is part of the AACC's celebration of National Library Week.
DTEND:20260409T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260408T030600Z
DTSTART:20260409T190000Z
GEO:35.787562;-78.669711
LOCATION:D.H. Hill Jr. Library\, Fishbowl Forum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Create Your Own Library: A Book Binding and Bookstagram Workshop
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52456319776697
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/create-your-own-library-a-book-binding-
 and-bookstagram-workshop
END:VEVENT
